      "content": "The weight of grief is crushing, and it's a constant ache that you can't escape. The space in the bed is a painful reminder that you're no longer the only one occupying it, and it's almost too much to bear. It's as if you're stuck in limbo, unable to progress from the heartbreak that has shattered your world. The thought of going on, of finding meaning again, feels like an impossible task.",
